{"type":"message","id":"ef0ee763","parentId":"1c893d93","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:13:00.762Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pulse ran successfully. Now let me read the most recent session log (the one from 001230, which is the one that was just created).","thinkingSignature":"d64118c577d6115f998e240d64240ac8465a98c2209b5f260b0160a29f168a2a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_z6rawnetbegk_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-24 001230.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":877,"output":84,"cacheRead":11878,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12839,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774325576762}}
{"type":"message","id":"ca6a36b7","parentId":"ef0ee763","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:13:00.772Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_z6rawnetbegk_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 001230\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n2. There's a pending TIC Experiment (Temporal Invariance Compression)\r\n3. Next action is to implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n\r\nThe key insight from this session is the \"COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\" - the hypothesis that causal structure IS invariant structure. The next step is to implement the TIC classifier.\r\n\r\nSo my action should be to:\r\n- Create a TIC classifier implementation\r\n- This should analyze the pulse logs and identify invariant vs variant patterns\r\n- Then use those invariants to predict next pulse content\r\n\r\nLet me implement a TIC classifier. I'll create a Python script that:\r\n1. Loads pulse logs from the logs directory\r\n2. Extracts content patterns\r\n3. Classifies invariant vs variant elements\r\n4. Tests prediction of next pulse content\r\n\r\nI should start by examining the pulse log structure, then implement the classifier.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that identifies invariants across pulse logs and tests prediction accuracy.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `temporal_invariance_classifier.py` - a Python script that reads pulse logs, extracts structural invariants, classifies invariant/variant elements, and tests next-pulse prediction accuracy against the success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```python\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTemporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n\r\nSuccess criteria:\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nimport json\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\nLOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\n\r\ndef extract_pulse_sections(content):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract named sections from a pulse log.\"\"\"\r\n    sections = {}\r\n    current_section = \"header\"\r\n    current_content = []\r\n    \r\n    for line in content.split('\\n'):\r\n        match = re.match(r'^##\\s+(.+)$', line)\r\n        if match:\r\n            if current_content:\r\n                sections[current_section] = '\\n'.join(current_content).strip()\r\n            current_section = match.group(1).lower()\r\n            current_content = []\r\n        else:\r\n            current_content.append(line)\r\n    \r\n    if current_content:\r\n        sections[current_section] = '\\n'.join(current_content).strip()\r\n    \r\n    return sections\r\n\r\ndef extract_tokens(text):\r\n    \"\"\"Simple tokenizer for structural analysis.\"\"\"\r\n    tokens = re.findall(r'\\b\\w+\\b', text.lower())\r\n    return [t for t in tokens if len(t) > 2]\r\n\r\ndef compute_ngram_invariants(pulse_tokens, n=3):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract n-grams as potential invariants.\"\"\"\r\n    ngrams = []\r\n    for i in range(len(pulse_tokens) - n + 1):\r\n        ngram = tuple(pulse_tokens[i:i+n])\r\n        ngrams.append(ngram)\r\n    return ngrams\r\n\r\ndef analyze_pulse_corpus():\r\n    \"\"\"Analyze all pulse logs for invariant patterns.\"\"\"\r\n    pulse_files = sorted(LOG_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"))\r\n    \r\n    if len(pulse_files) < 5:\r\n        print(f\"ERROR: Need at least 5 pulse logs, found {len(pulse_files)}\")\r\n        return None\r\n    \r\n    # Extract sections and tokens from all pulses\r\n    pulses = []\r\n    for pf in pulse_files:\r\n        content = pf.read_text(encoding='utf-8')\r\n        sections = extract_pulse_sections(content)\r\n        tokens = extract_tokens(content)\r\n        pulses.append({\r\n            'file': pf.name,\r\n            'sections': sections,\r\n            'tokens': tokens,\r\n            'ngrams': compute_ngram_invariants(tokens)\r\n        })\r\n    \r\n    # Count section name occurrences (structural invariants)\r\n    section_counts = Counter()\r\n    for p in pulses:\r\n        for section_name in p['sections'].keys():\r\n            section_counts[section_name] += 1\r\n    \r\n    # Invariants: sections appearing in >80% of pulses\r\n    threshold = 0.8 * len(pulse_files)\r\n    structural_invariants = [s for s, c in section_counts.items() if c >= threshold]\r\n    \r\n    # Token frequency analysis\r\n    all_tokens = []\r\n    for p in pulses:\r\n        all_tokens.extend(p['tokens'])\r\n    token_freq = Counter(all_tokens)\r\n    \r\n    # High-frequency tokens as semantic invariants\r\n    total_pulses = len(pulse_files)\r\n    semantic_invariants = [t for t, c in token_freq.items() \r\n                          if c >= threshold and t not in ['the', 'and', 'for', 'are', 'but']]\r\n    \r\n    return {\r\n        'pulse_count': len(pulse_files),\r\n        'structural_invariants': structural_invariants,\r\n        'semantic_invariants': semantic_invariants[:20],  # Top 20\r\n        'token_freq': token_freq.most_common(30)\r\n    }\r\n\r\ndef classify_invariant_variants(pulse_content, invariants):\r\n    \"\"\"Classify content elements as invariant or variant.\"\"\"\r\n    structural_inv = invariants.get('structural_invariants', [])\r\n    semantic_inv = set(invariants.get('semantic_invariants', []))\r\n    \r\n    sections = extract_pulse_sections(pulse_content)\r\n    classification = {'invariant': [], 'variant': []}\r\n    \r\n    for section_name, section_content in sections.items():\r\n        if section_name in structural_inv:\r\n            classification['invariant'].append(section_name)\r\n        else:\r\n            classification['variant'].append(section_name)\r\n    \r\n    # Classify key\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 00:12:52\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774325580770}}
